hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Photon sphere equation and roots:
$$r^2-3Mr+2Q^2=0\,. $$
Roots:
$$r=\frac{3M\pm\sqrt{9M^2-8Q^2}}{2}\,. $$

2. Substitute $Q=\tfrac23M$, so $Q^2=\tfrac49M^2$:
$$9M^2-8Q^2=9M^2-\frac{32}{9}M^2=\frac{49}{9}M^2,\qquad 
\sqrt{9M^2-8Q^2}=\frac{7}{3}M.$$
Larger root:
$$r_{ph}=\frac{3M+\frac{7}{3}M}{2}
=\frac{\frac{9}{3}M+\frac{7}{3}M}{2}
=\frac{\frac{16}{3}M}{2}
=\frac{8}{3}M.$$

3. Metric function at $r_{ph}$:
$$f(r)=1-\frac{2M}{r}+\frac{Q^2}{r^2},$$
so
$$f(r_{ph})
=1-\frac{2M}{\frac{8}{3}M}+\frac{\frac{4}{9}M^2}{\bigl(\frac{8}{3}M\bigr)^2}
=1-\frac{6}{8}+\frac{4/9}{64/9}
=1-\frac{3}{4}+\frac{1}{16}
=1-\frac{12}{16}+\frac{1}{16}
=\frac{5}{16}.$$

4. Shadow radius:
$$r_{sh}=\frac{r_{ph}}{\sqrt{f(r_{ph})}}
=\frac{\frac{8}{3}M}{\sqrt{\frac{5}{16}}}
=\frac{8}{3}M\cdot\frac{4}{\sqrt5}
=\frac{32}{3\sqrt5}M
=\frac{32\sqrt5}{15}M.$$
